        <div class="faq-wrapper" id="faq">

            <header class="faq-header">
                <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
                <p class="faq-subtitle">If you don't find what you're looking for, contact directly — all inquiries are confidential.</p>
            </header>

            <div class="faq-body">

                <section class="faq-group" aria-labelledby="faq-group-1">
                    <h2 id="faq-group-1">Is this for me?</h2>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Is this like antivirus or a VPN?</summary>
                        <p>No. Antivirus and VPNs are generic, always-on tools. This is a one-time expert hardening of your specific devices, accounts, and threat exposure — applied in person, calibrated to your situation.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>How is this different from IT support?</summary>
                        <p>IT support fixes problems after they happen. This is hardening, threat modeling, and training. It eliminates the many technical and non-technical vulnerabilities before anyone exploits them — using the same endpoint hardening standards applied to government systems.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Do you work with individuals or only companies?</summary>
                        <p>Individuals only. The service exists for people in high-pressure personal situations — separation, dispute, inheritance, competitive exposure — not for corporate IT procurement.</p>
                    </details>
                </section>

                <section class="faq-group" aria-labelledby="faq-group-2">
                    <h2 id="faq-group-2">Confidentiality</h2>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Is the consultation confidential? Will anyone know I contacted you?</summary>
                        <p>Yes, completely. No notes are shared with anyone. Contact via WhatsApp or Signal is end-to-end encrypted — nothing passes through a contact form or third-party system.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Do you keep records of what you found on my device?</summary>
                        <p>No. What's found during the engagement is addressed during the engagement. Nothing is logged, copied, or stored.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Is there a file on me somewhere after the engagement?</summary>
                        <p>No. The only document that leaves the engagement is the Certificate of Hardening — a signed record that the work was done. It stays with you. No copy is retained.</p>
                    </details>
                </section>

                <section class="faq-group" aria-labelledby="faq-group-3">
                    <h2 id="faq-group-3">What actually happens?</h2>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Can this be done online or remotely?</summary>
                        <p>No. Remote access is a backdoor into your device — giving it to a security provider is no different from giving it to anyone else. Everything is done in person, in your presence, on your timeline.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Where do you operate? Will you come to me?</summary>
                        <p>Yes — I come to you. Primarily Israel; international engagements by arrangement.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>How long does an engagement take?</summary>
                        <p>Personal Shield: one day. Extended Shield: two to four days. Inner Circle Shield depends on the number of people covered. The schedule is agreed before the engagement begins.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>What do I need to bring or prepare?</summary>
                        <p>Your devices and all your account credentials — which you enter yourself; we never handle passwords. Bring your account details, your story, and any evidence of suspicious activity you may have seen. Everything else is handled on-site.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>What is the Certificate of Hardening?</summary>
                        <p>A signed document issued at the end of the engagement confirming the specific hardening steps applied, the standards used, and the date. Yours to keep; no copy retained.</p>
                    </details>
                </section>

                <section class="faq-group" aria-labelledby="faq-group-4">
                    <h2 id="faq-group-4">Who is doing this?</h2>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Who does the work?</summary>
                        <p>Dr. Lior Tabansky — directly. Not a team, not a junior technician supervised remotely. The person who assesses your threat is the person who hardens your devices and accounts.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Can I verify Dr. Tabansky's background independently?</summary>
                        <p>Yes. The full research record — publications, academic positions, government advisory roles, media appearances — is at <a href="https://cyberdrtabansky.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cyberdrtabansky.com</a>. It's publicly available so you can verify without taking our word for it.</p>
                    </details>
                </section>

                <section class="faq-group" aria-labelledby="faq-group-5">
                    <h2 id="faq-group-5">Pricing and tiers</h2>
                    <details>
                        <summary>How much does it cost?</summary>
                        <p>Four tiers, depending on scope:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Personal Shield — ₪15,000.</strong> One person, primary device, all accounts, two hardware security keys, Certificate of Hardening. One day.</li>
                            <li><strong>Extended Shield — ₪32,000.</strong> Everything in Personal, plus home network hardening, vehicle security audit, and connected devices. Two to four days.</li>
                            <li><strong>Inner Circle Shield — ₪38,000.</strong> Everything in Personal for typically three people on the same side — family members or a close professional circle. Each person fully hardened.</li>
                            <li><strong>Sovereign Shield — ₪95,000.</strong> All of the above, plus physical counter-surveillance sweep, Annual Threat Monitoring, and Priority Retainer — included.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>A Threat Assessment costs ₪3,500 and is credited in full toward any protection tier purchased within 14 days.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>What's the difference between the tiers?</summary>
                        <p>Personal Shield covers one person's primary device and accounts. Extended Shield adds the physical environment — home network, vehicle, connected devices. Inner Circle Shield adds people: typically three individuals, each fully hardened. Sovereign Shield is comprehensive — all of the above plus physical counter-surveillance and ongoing monitoring included in the price.</p>
                        <p>The hardening standard is identical across all tiers. The difference is scope, not quality.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>What is the Threat Assessment, and do I need it?</summary>
                        <p>The Threat Assessment (₪3,500) is a structured, in-person review of your current exposure — devices, accounts, network, situation. It produces a threat map and a recommended scope of work. If you proceed with a protection tier within 14 days, the ₪3,500 is credited in full.</p>
                        <p>It's not required — some clients come with a clear picture of what they need. But if you're unsure which tier fits, it's the right starting point.</p>
                    </details>
                </section>

                <section class="faq-group" aria-labelledby="faq-group-6">
                    <h2 id="faq-group-6">After the engagement</h2>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Is the protection permanent?</summary>
                        <p>The hardening applied is durable. Devices stay hardened. Accounts stay secured. Hardware keys don't expire. What changes over time is the threat landscape — new vulnerabilities, credential leaks, evolving attack methods. That's what Annual Threat Monitoring addresses.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>What are Annual Threat Monitoring and the Priority Retainer?</summary>
                        <p>Two ongoing products available to all past clients. Annual Threat Monitoring (₪6,000/year): external threat watching — dark web credential leak scanning, breach alerts, CVEs affecting your device profile, and one in-person account hygiene check per year. Priority Retainer (₪12,000/year): 8 business-hour response SLA and three in-person check-in sessions per year.</p>
                        <p>Neither requires remote access to your devices. Both are included in Sovereign Shield.</p>
                    </details>
                </section>

